ies and procedures that address child sexual abuse complaints directed at paid and volunteer faith community representatives and/ or leaders. She identifies differences and common themes among the approaches taken by the institutions and provides a summary table for an accessible comparative overview. Child sexual abuse is not new, but the emergence of policies to address abuse complaints within religious institutions is. This book identifies significant and shared causal factors behind the emergence of policy and reviews their content carefully. This review will serve as a significant tool for furthering the development of such policies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAbus sexuels à l'égard des enfants par des membres du clergéxCanada. 0aAbus sexuels à l'égard des enfantsxAspect religieuxxChristianismexHistoire des doctrines. 0aAbus sexuels à l'égard des enfantsxPréventionxCanadaxCanada. 0aChild sexual abuse by clergyxCanada. 0aChild sexual abuse by clergyzCanada. 0aChild sexual abusexPreventionxCanada. 0aChild sexual abusexReligious aspectsxChristianityxHistory of doctrines. 0aChild sexual abusezCanadaxPrevention. 4aFamily & Relationships: Child Abuse. 4aLaw: Child Advocacy. 4aReligion. 7aRELIGION / Ethics.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2012z978311127413308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2012z978311127716540uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978155458407940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781554584079423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781554584079/original  a978-3-11-127413-3  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2012b2012  a978-3-11-127716-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2012b2012  aGBV-deGruyter-alles